cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

The paper discusses advanced motor skills for robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses robot learning from human demonstration, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions handling partly soft partly rigid objects, which could involve computer vision (cs.CV) for object recognition and manipulation. Finally, the paper discusses the physical success of the nunchaku flipping challenge, which involves control and coordination, and could fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
